e same time, it offers important contributions to understanding different Middle English genres: romance, dream vision, drama and fabliau.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEnglish literatureyMiddle English, 1100-1500xHistory and criticism. 0aSleep in literature. 4aLiterature Studies 2022. 70(DE-588)4014777-00(DE-627)1063387490(DE-576)208909400aEnglisch2gnd 70(DE-588)4035964-50(DE-627)1062450150(DE-576)209015608aLiteratur2gnd 70(DE-588)4129108-60(DE-627)1045354740(DE-576)209607793aMittelalter2gnd 70(DE-588)4179659-70(DE-627)1053319880(DE-576)209992832aSchlafgMotiv2gnd 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh  aChaucer.  aMiddle English.  adreams.  aemotions.  aethics.  aliterature.  amedieval.  aromance.  asleep.  aspace.1 aLeitch, Megan G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packagez978311128198840uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152615111740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526151117423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526151117/original  a978-3-11-128198-8  Manchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packageb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles